column5: Can anyone tell me a good live bait store around Cambridge area? I see place in Preston closed down and was wondering so when I go ice fishing hopefully. Suckers , shiners etc
catch'em bait in kitchener. Kirby has been closed for months now.
Tall Tales closed?  That sucks, I liked Pat.

Tall Tales closed?  That sucks, I liked Pat. Yes talked to Pat and he said he cannot compete with the big stores that people go to know and they dont even know what they are selling so he closed up last year
He was working at Sail here. Thats the last time I saw him though. I would like to get my hands on the tanks he had there.

I will try out the Kitchener place then. When it gets colder I'm going to try shades mill for pike. You guys had any luck there with minnows? And I don't know who pat is but the guys at sail are really kind and great help! I hope he's doing good.
Kingsway tackle in Guelph on Woodlawn, or natural sports in kitchener also carry live bait if your headed north.
Get Bent on HWY 6 north just past the CDN Tire at Woodlawn
